Qruakpit
========

A Rust + Tauri fork of Quakpit (https://github.com/Ooble-Studio/QuakPit) by Ooble Studio (https://ooble.studio).

The original Quakpit is MIT-licensed. This fork:
- Re-implements the application in Rust (Tauri v2) and React.
- Vendors the original art and sound assets ('blade.png', 'head-duck.png',
  'plane-red.png', 'plane-red-base.png', 'thumb-head-duck.png',
  'thumb-plane-red.png', 'quack.wav', 'logo.png', and the bundled OFL fonts)
  from the upstream repository under their original MIT license. See
  LICENSE-quakpit for the upstream license text.
- Adds Microsoft Outlook calendar support via Microsoft Graph.
- Removes the Polar.sh-backed "Pro" license check; all previously gated
  features (extra plane colours, character heads, sound packs, banner themes,
  flight speeds, custom flier image, and multi-calendar support) are unlocked
  for everyone.

Bundled fonts:
- Caveat and Patrick Hand under the SIL Open Font License v1.1. See
  src/assets/fonts/OFL.txt for the full text.

